The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 EMC offers data storage facility at bargain price

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Nov. 21: Data storage and management company EMC Corporation plans to tap the small and medium business (SMB) segment with its entry-level product priced below Rs 2 lakh. 

 The company is targeting the growing sectors like manufacturing, IT and ITeS, government, telecom, banking and financial services, pharmaceuticals and healthcare, education and services.

 The focus is shifting to the SMB segment, elaborated Abhrajit Bhattacharjee, manager-marketing and corporate affairs, EMC. Mid-sized enterprises and SMBs in India today need to do more with less. With their information need growing exponentially versus the marginal increase in IT spend, companies in this segment find it difficult to manage and protect huge amount of critical data in the most effective way.

 The new product will address the backup, retrieval, archiving, business continuity and data consolidation requirement of the small and medium businesses across the sectors.

 Industry sources pointed out that SMBs were expected to increase their spending on data storage by 150 per cent this year compared with Rs 1,975 crore last year.

 According to IDC estimates, EMC is the largest external storage vendor in the country with a market share of 24.5 per cent followed closely by Hewlett-Packard at 23.2 per cent.

 Bhattacharjee said, The data storage market for the SMB segment has seen a growth of over 35 per cent while the enterprise space is growing between 12-14 per cent against the industry average of 18 per cent.

 EMC is also expecting business growth in smaller cities like Jaipur, Chandigarh and Ahmedabad. 




